Today was Practice #119 for me and unfortunately my truth is that I feel myself becoming disenchanted with yoga üòî. I dont want to stop because Im proud of myself for showing up almost every day and doing the best I can. I also have a hard time with aerobic exercise or anything high impact because of arthritis, so yoga has been the perfect answer for me.  But every day I read the comments and never once have I had the emotional release (unless you count anger or frustration, and even then it didnt involve tears) that every one else has and I just cant bring myself to buy into things like chakras, chanting, or having a 3rd eye.  Ive tried to find my own ways to work thru those things, and some days Im more successful than others, but most days I just end up feeling like I dont belong.  I had set a goal for myself to do 365 yoga practices, and I dont want to give it up because I love the physical challenges, but I cant keep leaving the mat feeling emotionally worse than when I started which seems to be the case most days lately.  Im very conflicted right now.

I am really enjoying this revolution and it has got me thinking about looking further into meditation.  I realise while following this series of videos, I really need to time to just look within and focus on myself instead of pushing myself through so I hope once day 31 is up, I can look to meditation and also continue with these yoga videos, although I don't know what one to turn on next.  It has been a great motivational tool for me as I haven't been so focused on making my day fulfilling in such a long time ... It is good to finally get a routine going again and I am just focused on making it all continue on during the next week.

I am working it out in my head when to have time for yoga, for meditation and for exercise inbetween family commitments ... but if I got this far, I can get through one week ...

Wow that was really insightful! I re-discovered what my friends have been telling me, probably on a deeper level this time. I'm very hard on myself even with things that improve my life like my discipline for writing early in the morning, my exercise training, my work ethic etc...I'm not going crazy with negative thoughts, but I don't give myself time to praise, enjoy and feel good about it all. And I realized that I don't have to be hard on myself to grow and improve in anything. Like...I literally just discovered that. lol. I've probably preached that to friends of mine in the past too lol. So my revolution this year is to use love for myself to do the same things and grow in the same areas of my life that I have grown in, previously using 'hard' talk, like 'you can do better,' or 'good, but you're not there yet.' Instead, it will be stuff like, 'you're doing great and more, amazing growth is on its way,' and 'intense workout, now love your body and thank it with great nutrition so it stays and becomes stronger.' So a big thank you! Oh and as soon as you did the 'rock out' gesture, I thought of this video (1000 people singing/playing the Foo Fighter's song, "Learn to Fly" - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JozAmXo2bDE
